replies.bodyText:
Not sure I follow. Can we not de-dup the methods by making them static, e.g.,
private Code canMakeCliRequest() { ... }

becomes
static Code canMakeCliRequest(final TestKsqlRestApp restApp, final Map<String, String> clientProps) { ... }

(and similarly for the others)?

Then to keep the individual tests cleaner each can have:
private Code canMakeCliRequest() {
    return canMakeCliRequest(REST_APP, clientProps);
}

(and similar).
These methods would still have to be duplicated between the two tests but they seem tiny enough and the actual implementation of the helper methods would only appear in one place. WDYT?

